TextEng: Who are you? A better question, perhaps, is what are you doing in the Tower? You don't seem like one of Maugrim's toadies.
Text: 넌 누구지? 더 나은 질문은 아마... 탑에서 뭘 하고 있느냐는 거겠지. 모그림의 아첨꾼 같아 보이진 않는데.

TextEng: Mmmm... a rather delicious looking <race> creature, is it? What a treat. Please don't tell me you're one of the fools toadying after Maugrim.
Text: 음... 꽤 먹음직스러운 <race>로군, 그렇지 않아? 진수성찬이야. 설마 모그림한테 아부하는 바보들 중 하나라고 말하진 않겠지?

TextEng: Hmph. You can't be one of Maugrim's fools. You haven't the look of fanatic desperation to you.
Text: 흥. 모그림의 바보들 중 하나일 리가 없어. 광신도 특유의 필사적인 눈빛이 없잖아.

TextEng: Ohhhh, my... and it has the intellectual capacity of a footstool, as well. Like a boon from the sky, you are.
Text: 어머나... 지능도 발판 수준이라니. 하늘이 내려준 선물이야, 너.

TextEng: I don't know why you wouldn't enjoy my glances, male... certainly you must receive enough of them. I think I would remember one such as you... you are a stranger, here.
Text: 왜 내 시선을 즐기지 않는 거야, 남자... 분명 그런 눈길 많이 받아봤을 텐데. 너 같은 사람이라면 기억했을 텐데... 여긴 처음이구나.

TextEng: I would admit you've a look to you, <male/female>. A smell that is similarly unflattering... but no, you're no fanatic.
Text: 인정하지, <male/female>, 넌 뭔가 있어. 냄새도 비슷하게 별로지만... 그래도 광신도는 아니야.

TextEng: You don't know who I am, <male/female>? Well... that certainly means that you aren't native to the Brotherhood. A stranger, then.
Text: 내가 누군지 모른다고, <male/female>? 글쎄... 그렇다면 분명 결사단 출신은 아니겠네. 이방인이로군.

TextEng: Hmmm. You don't know of Maugrim... or you feign ignorance, which no fanatic of his would even conceive of. A stranger, then.
Text: 흠. 모그림을 모른다... 아니면 모르는 척하는 건가. 그의 광신도라면 상상도 못 할 짓이지. 이방인이로군.

TextEng: Ahhh, it appears I have an intellect of staggering proportions to deal with, now. Do calm yourself, <male/female>, I'm sure your brain could use the energy.
Text: 아아, 대단한 지성을 상대하게 됐군. 진정해, <male/female>, 그 에너지는 머리 쓰는 데 아껴둬.

TextEng: You certainly needn't worry about any tricks from me. If I had intended to harm you, don't you think I would have already done so?
Text: 내게서 속임수를 걱정할 필요는 없어. 널 해치려 했다면, 벌써 그렇게 하지 않았겠어?

TextEng: So you aren't one of Maugrim's. I would know if you were one of Arklem's. The only question, then, how did you come to be this deep within the Host Tower?
Text: 그러니까 모그림 쪽은 아니군. 아클렘 쪽이면 알아봤을 테고. 그렇다면 유일한 의문은, 어떻게 중심탑 이렇게 깊숙이 들어왔느냐는 거지?

TextEng: By all means. Ask away, <male/female>.
Text: 물론이지. 마음껏 물어봐, <male/female>.

TextEng: An evasive answer... and far from the truth, no doubt. Or do you truly expect me to believe that you haplessly wandered past the Tower's wards?
Text: 둘러대는군... 진실과는 거리가 멀어 보여. 정말 탑의 결계를 우연히 지나쳤다고 믿으라는 건 아니겠지?

TextEng: Oh, I suppose it's possible that Maugrim was stupid enough that he removed the spells from the bridge... but I doubt it. Regardless, who am I to question your word?
Text: 아, 모그림이 다리의 마법을 풀 정도로 멍청했을 수도 있겠지... 하지만 의심스럽군. 어쨌든, 네 말을 의심할 처지는 아니지.

TextEng: A noble goal. I wouldn't put such a feat past you, either... you must have managed to bypass the wards on the bridge and the guards, after all.
Text: 숭고한 목표로군. 네가 해낼 수 있을 거라 생각해... 다리의 결계와 경비를 어떻게든 뚫고 왔으니까.

TextEng: Maugrim will be no simple task to overcome, but somehow I doubt that will deter you. Don't let me keep you from your task, by all means.
Text: 모그림을 이기는 건 쉬운 일이 아니겠지만, 그렇다고 네가 물러설 것 같진 않군. 내가 방해하진 않을게, 편히 가.

TextEng: Well, there could be any one of a number of answers. Omniscience, divining spells galore, incredibly high intelligence... take your pick.
Text: 글쎄, 여러 가지 답이 있을 수 있지. 전지전능, 수많은 점술 주문, 엄청나게 높은 지능... 골라봐.

TextEng: How do I know all these things? Omniscience, divinations, incredible intelligence... take your pick. Do let me know if I'm talking too fast for you.
Text: 이걸 어떻게 아냐고? 전지전능, 점술, 대단한 지능... 골라봐. 너무 빨리 말하면 알려줘.

TextEng: Normally I would object to someone answering a question with a question, but I imagine you do that a lot. It's all right... I've no need to pry.
Text: 보통은 질문에 질문으로 답하는 거 싫어하는데, 넌 그게 습관인 것 같군. 괜찮아... 캐묻진 않을게.

TextEng: Technically that's not a question, it's a request. It is rather nice of you to ask, however... my name is Nyphithys. I am pleased to meet you, <male/female>.
Text: 엄밀히 말하면 그건 질문이 아니라 요청이지. 하지만 물어봐 줘서 기쁘군... 내 이름은 니피시스야. 반가워, <male/female>.

TextEng: Maugrim is the new Archmage Arcane of the Brotherhood, a position he took by force. Arklem, the former Archmage, fled while he could.
Text: 모그림은 결사단의 새 비전 대마법사야, 무력으로 그 자리를 빼앗았지. 전임 대마법사 아클렘은 도망칠 수 있을 때 도망쳤고.

TextEng: You know this, however, do you not? As for where Maugrim is... that I have no idea of. I am unaware of anything beyond the confines of this room.
Text: 이건 알고 있겠지? 모그림이 어디 있는지는... 모르겠어. 이 방 밖의 일은 알 수가 없거든.

TextEng: You mean physically? Or do you simply wish to know what has happened to leave it strewn with religious fanatics and dead wizards?
Text: 물리적으로? 아니면 종교적 광신도와 죽은 마법사들이 널브러져 있게 된 경위를 알고 싶은 거야?

TextEng: If you want to know what is occurring in it now, well... that's the one thing I cannot help you with. I am aware of nothing beyond the confines of this room.
Text: 지금 무슨 일이 벌어지고 있는지 알고 싶다면, 글쎄... 그건 도와줄 수 없어. 이 방 밖의 일은 알 수가 없거든.

TextEng: Not the curious type, I see. That's quite all right... I'm more used to working with mages and their insatiable quest for power and knowledge, but I can adapt.
Text: 호기심이 많은 편은 아니군. 괜찮아... 권력과 지식에 굶주린 마법사들을 상대하는 데 더 익숙하지만, 적응할 수 있어.

TextEng: I would be more than willing to answer your questions in full or do whatever else you wish... but first, I would ask a boon of you.
Text: 네 질문에 모두 답해주거나 원하는 건 뭐든 해줄 수 있어... 하지만 먼저, 부탁 하나만 들어줘.

TextEng: Do you see that brazier on the other side of the room? It contains a spell that keeps me from leaving. Would you be so kind as to destroy it?
Text: 방 저쪽에 있는 화로 보여? 저기에 날 가두는 주문이 담겨 있어. 부숴줄 수 있겠어?

TextEng: Before you run off, allow me to ask a boon of you, <male/female>. It is a very small thing, believe me.
Text: 달려가기 전에, 부탁 하나 해도 될까, <male/female>. 아주 작은 일이야, 믿어줘.

TextEng: Hmmm. There isn't much that you don't notice, is there? You are quite correct, <male/female>... all is not quite as it seems.
Text: 흠. 눈치가 빠르군, 그렇지? 맞아, <male/female>... 모든 게 보이는 대로는 아니야.

TextEng: This is a prison, this room I am in. I am quite stuck... though perhaps your arrival is an opportunity for me to escape.
Text: 이 방은 감옥이야. 꼼짝없이 갇혀 있어... 하지만 네가 나타난 건 탈출의 기회일지도 모르겠군.

TextEng: Do you believe I would stand here in this room for some other reason? Waiting for the odd chance that you might stumble upon me, perhaps?
Text: 다른 이유로 이 방에 서 있다고 생각해? 혹시나 네가 우연히 들어올까 기다리면서?

TextEng: There is no way to prove my words, I suppose. You are free to ask me whatever you like, of course.
Text: 내 말을 증명할 방법은 없겠지. 물론 원하는 건 뭐든 물어봐도 돼.

TextEng: Hmmm. I don't believe it is anything other than a regular brazier that Maugrim anchored his spell to. You are free to investigate it for yourself, however.
Text: 흠. 모그림이 주문을 고정시킨 평범한 화로일 뿐이라고 생각해. 직접 조사해봐도 좋아.

TextEng: If it does explode, that would be incredibly inconvenient, seeing as I would be caught in the same explosion as you.
Text: 폭발하면 꽤 곤란하겠지, 나도 같이 휘말릴 테니까.

TextEng: Well, let's see. I still have a magic item, if you would like it. Or would you prefer a reward more... personal?
Text: 어디 보자. 마법 물품이 있긴 해, 원하면 줄게. 아니면... 좀 더 사적인 보상이 좋아?

TextEng: Oh? Are you saying you would prefer to see me left here, trapped? I have a magic item, here, to offer as reward, if need be.
Text: 오? 날 여기 갇혀 있게 두겠다는 거야? 마법 물품으로 보상할 수 있는데, 필요하다면.

TextEng: Well, let's see. I do have a magic item, still, that I would be more than willing to offer you. I can direct you to more, as well, if you like.
Text: 글쎄, 어디 보자. 기꺼이 줄 수 있는 마법 물품이 아직 있어. 원한다면 더 있는 곳도 알려줄 수 있고.

TextEng: So I can watch you walk out the door and have nothing at all to offer the next <male/female> who stumbles in here? Not likely.
Text: 네가 문 밖으로 나가는 걸 지켜보고, 다음에 여기 들어오는 <male/female>한테 줄 게 아무것도 없게 되라고? 그럴 리가.

TextEng: I can offer you plenty... more than you suspect, I imagine... if you simply help me to free myself from this prison. What do you say?
Text: 많은 걸 줄 수 있어... 네 생각보다 훨씬 많이... 이 감옥에서 날 풀어주기만 하면. 어때?

TextEng: So it's greed, is it? Well... there's all kinds of things you would no doubt like to have right here in the Tower, with no one particularly guarding them.
Text: 욕심 때문이군? 글쎄... 이 탑엔 네가 탐낼 만한 온갖 것들이 있어, 딱히 지키는 사람도 없이.

TextEng: So your concern would be what? What I intend to do after you free me? Whether I am a good person or not?
Text: 그래서 걱정이 뭔데? 풀어주고 나서 내가 뭘 할 건지? 내가 좋은 사람인지 아닌지?

TextEng: I intend to find Arklem once you free me, to be truthful. I doubt you and I will meet again. Beyond that, ask me whatever you wish.
Text: 솔직히 말하면, 풀려나면 아클렘을 찾을 생각이야. 너와 다시 만날 일은 없을 거야. 그 외에는 뭐든 물어봐.

TextEng: I see. I do not appreciate being disregarded so, <male/female>. Are you sure you will not change your mind?
Text: 그렇군. 이렇게 무시당하는 건 싫은데, <male/female>. 정말 마음 안 바꿀 거야?

TextEng: Then what keeps you from aiding me? Will you destroy the brazier or not? It is a simple enough act.
Text: 그럼 뭐가 문제야? 화로를 부술 거야 말 거야? 간단한 일인데.

TextEng: You are amusing yourself, I see. Perhaps I failed to mention that while I couldn't leave this room... it certainly doesn't prevent me from killing you!
Text: 재밌어하는군. 아마 말 안 했나 본데, 이 방을 떠날 순 없어도... 널 죽이는 건 막지 못해!

TextEng: What will I do about it? Well, let's see. Did I mention that the spell on the brazier doesn't prevent me from killing you? Perhaps not.
Text: 내가 뭘 할 것 같냐고? 글쎄, 어디 보자. 화로의 주문이 널 죽이는 걸 막지 못한다고 말했던가? 아마 안 했겠지.

TextEng: That is too bad. I would have enjoyed freedom. As it is, I shall have to be satisfied with a little carnage.
Text: 안됐군. 자유를 즐겼을 텐데. 이렇게 된 이상, 약간의 학살로 만족해야겠어.

TextEng: That is a relief. Please proceed... I am eager to be away from this cramped little room.
Text: 다행이군. 진행해줘... 이 비좁은 방에서 빨리 벗어나고 싶어.

TextEng: Then what shall it be? Will you destroy the brazier or not? It is a simple enough act.
Text: 그래서 어떻게 할 건데? 화로를 부술 거야 말 거야? 간단한 일이잖아.

TextEng: I would be perfectly capable of doing so, I assure you... if I could reach it. Unfortunately the spell that restricts my movement falls just short of the brazier.
Text: 할 수 있으면 벌써 했겠지... 닿기만 하면 말이야. 안타깝게도 내 움직임을 제한하는 주문이 화로 바로 앞까지밖에 안 미쳐.

TextEng: It would have been rather foolish of Maugrim to set up my prison otherwise, wouldn't you agree?
Text: 안 그랬으면 모그림이 감옥을 꽤 멍청하게 만든 거겠지, 안 그래?

TextEng: Their defenses? Well, I doubt Maugrim has had time to set most of the Tower's wards back up. With the right runestones, I suspect you could move throughout the halls at will.
Text: 방어라? 글쎄, 모그림이 탑의 결계를 다시 설치할 시간이 있었을지 의심스러워. 적절한 룬석만 있으면 복도를 마음대로 다닐 수 있을 거야.

TextEng: Maugrim himself will have taken over Arklem's sanctum, I suspect. It would fit with that fool's bloated sense of pride.
Text: 모그림 자신은 아클렘의 성소를 차지했을 거야. 그 바보의 부풀어 오른 자존심에 딱 맞거든.

TextEng: If you found Valinda Shadowmantle, I would wager she has a runestone to reach the sanctum. I bet there is a stone to reach her on this very level.
Text: 발린드라 섀도맨틀을 찾으면, 성소로 가는 룬석을 갖고 있을 거야. 이 층 어딘가에 그녀한테 가는 돌이 있을 거고.

TextEng: Now... is that enough? I could tell you more once you free me, I assure you.
Text: 자... 그 정도면 충분해? 풀어주면 더 말해줄 수 있어, 장담해.

TextEng: A wizard? Me? No... not quite. I am Nyphithys... advisor and assistant to Archmage Arklem, the deposed leader of the Brotherhood.
Text: 마법사? 나? 아니... 그건 아니야. 난 니피시스... 쫓겨난 결사단 지도자 아클렘 대마법사의 조언자이자 보좌관이지.

TextEng: That is... difficult to explain. Killing me would not serve Maugrim's purposes.
Text: 그건... 설명하기 어렵군. 날 죽여봐야 모그림의 목적에 도움이 안 되거든.

TextEng: About myself? No, not at all. As a matter of fact, I am beginning to grow weary of your questioning. Be quick about it.
Text: 나에 대해서? 아니, 전혀. 사실 네 질문에 지쳐가고 있어. 빨리 해.

TextEng: Evil is a subjective term, <male/female>. Unless you mean it in a more primordial sense... in which case, yes, I am evil. Does that disturb you?
Text: 악이란 건 주관적이야, <male/female>. 더 원초적인 의미로 말하는 거라면... 맞아, 난 악이지. 그게 불편해?

TextEng: It was I who told Arklem to flee. I am not about to lose an investment of so many years to some fool and his overambitious cult.
Text: 아클렘에게 도망치라고 한 건 나야. 수년간 공들인 걸 어떤 바보와 그의 야망에 찬 사교 때문에 날릴 순 없거든.

TextEng: (sigh) Because I bring him certain advantages, things his wizards could not provide for him.
Text: (한숨) 내가 그에게 특별한 이점을 주거든, 그의 마법사들은 줄 수 없는 것들 말이야.

TextEng: Then why the questions? I am no psychotic killer. I said I would reward you for freeing me and I shall.
Text: 그럼 왜 질문해? 난 미친 살인마가 아니야. 풀어주면 보상하겠다고 했고, 그럴 거야.

TextEng: And if I am not? If I was the influence behind Arklem's rule, what difference would that make to you? I tire of your questions, <male/female>.
Text: 아니라면? 내가 아클렘 통치의 배후였다면, 네게 무슨 상관이야? 네 질문에 지쳤어, <male/female>.

TextEng: A clever <race> <male/female> you are, indeed. I shall not fill in the blanks, however. You know what you know.
Text: 참 영리한 <race> <male/female>이군, 정말. 하지만 빈칸을 채워주진 않을 거야. 아는 만큼 아는 거지.

TextEng: It makes no difference, however. I'll have no more questions from you... tell me now: will you destroy the brazier or not?
Text: 하지만 상관없어. 더 이상 질문은 받지 않을 거야... 지금 말해. 화로를 부술 거야, 말 거야?

TextEng: You ask too many questions, <male/female>. I shall not fill in the blanks for you.
Text: 질문이 너무 많아, <male/female>. 빈칸을 채워주진 않을 거야.

TextEng: I mean that while it would be inconvenient to me, it would not prevent me from searching for Arklem... which Maugrim hopes to prevent.
Text: 내 말은 나한테 불편하겠지만, 아클렘을 찾는 걸 막지는 못한다는 거야... 모그림이 막으려는 게 바로 그거지.

TextEng: Well, that's hardly unexpected now, is it?
Text: 글쎄, 그건 별로 놀랍지 않지, 그렇지?

TextEng: I do not think it needs to be explained any further. Continue with your questions, if you wish.
Text: 더 설명할 필요 없을 것 같은데. 원하면 계속 질문해.

TextEng: What is the delay? Surely you cannot tell me you are having difficulty destroying the brazier.
Text: 왜 늦어지는 거야? 설마 화로 부수는 게 어렵다는 건 아니겠지.

TextEng: I will not be questioned any further, <male/female>. I am sure you know more than enough... now destroy the brazier before I grow impatient.
Text: 더 이상 질문은 안 받아, <male/female>. 충분히 알았을 거야... 내가 인내심 잃기 전에 화로를 부숴.

TextEng: And why is that? I am asking you to do nothing strenuous. Will you do it or not?
Text: 왜 그런데? 힘든 걸 부탁하는 것도 아닌데. 할 거야 말 거야?

TextEng: Then do so. I tire of waiting.
Text: 그럼 해. 기다리는 거 지쳤어.

TextEng: You have done well. Maugrim will be chagrined to know that some adventurer stumbled in to rescue me from his spell.
Text: 잘했어. 어떤 모험가가 우연히 들어와서 주문에서 날 구해줬다는 걸 알면 모그림이 분해하겠지.

TextEng: I am eager to be off in search of Arklem. It will be difficult to say where he might have hidden himself in his... condition. Regardless, the Tower will be ours again in time.
Text: 아클렘을 찾으러 빨리 떠나고 싶군. 그의... 상태에서 어디 숨었을지 알기 어렵겠지만. 어쨌든, 탑은 때가 되면 다시 우리 거야.

TextEng: As for you, <male/female>... you did your part. You freed me, and the reward is yours by right. Take this item and go.
Text: 너 말이야, <male/female>... 네 몫은 다 했어. 날 풀어줬으니, 보상은 당연히 네 거야. 이걸 갖고 가.

TextEng: I suggest that you not still be present in the Host Tower when I return.
Text: 내가 돌아올 때까지 중심탑에 있진 말라고 충고해두지.
